{
  "texts": [
    "He doesn't care a damn about me\" (ibid, p. 51).",
    "\"It's quite obvious that you don't care two straws for me\" (ibid, p. 61).",
    "… she pull out of love with him (ibid, p. 64).",
    "\"By God, it's grand to be one's own mistress\" (ibid, p. 66).The only analysed work that is comparable to W.S.",
    "Maugham's Theatre in terms of both quantity and quality of phraseological units is J. Galsworthy's The Man of Property."
  ]
}